column2: Rainy- windy weather lately- light waves- 4-6" today
Windy but no white caps on the water.
Water is not green- brown- dark- or clear- sediment under water around disc travels in waves- pH 7.
Very calm- very green filamentous on surface- and the water is rushing over dam. Highest water level I've seen in 50 years!  Lake level: very high
Water quite rough but no white caps.  There is a southwest wind.
Partly cloudy and there are heavy waves.
Sunshine and medium ripples on the water.
Over 8" of rain in the last 10 days. Windy- stormy- cloudy and stirred up water.
Increasing winds- heavy rolling waves- lots of water-skiers on weekend.
Partly cloudy- waited for sunshine between clouds- very windy.
Light waves- lakes considerably lower than last year.
Water really choppy- 3/4" of ice on thoroughfare between Island and McCann Lake- final test for 1987.
Clear- sun slightly hazy- light waves
Bright sun- light breeze- low ripples
Sunny- some clouds- very little fall color yet
Bright sun- very rough- wind coming up fast
Bright sun- a little choppy- no chunky algae
Bright sun- lt. ripple- a few boats- 1 eagle- several gulls- beavers building on top of concrete dam ! !
Cold- breezy- partly cloudy- waited for sun b/w clouds
Hazy sun- has been windy + rainy
Partly cloudy- med. waves- sampled between clouds
Strong NE winds coming- test site is NE part of lake- wasn't too rough
Sunny- med. ripple- 2 fast boats with multiple skiers violently disturbing water- fish at risk
Sunny- med. waves- a few sea gulls
Conditions excellent for this time of year
Nice sun- med. waves- dark water
Sunny- water temp: 34 F- air temp: 40's- 40 degrees warmer a few days ago- need more cards
Sunny- about a dozen fishing boats- water skiers- 75 F
Clear- windy- some waves- no water over dam
Green slime on top of water- lake very calm
Light ripples- some algae- partly cloudy.
Water running over Swift Creek dam.
Weather is clear- lake calm.  Ice off on 4/21/93- algae on surface.  Lake level: very high
Clear- slight ripple.  Lake level: very high
Sunny- slight ripples.  Lake level: very high
Clear skies- ripple- lots of floating algae- 6.6" rain last 5 days.  Lake level: very high
Clear skies- sunny- small waves- becoming over run with aquatic plants and weeds
Clear sky- 4" waves- water color quite blue today.
Clear skies- 3" ripples- algae is moderately heavy.
Ice off 4/9/94.  Ducks- geese and loons are on the lake.  Water calm- skies clear.  Beautiful day.
Sunny- windy- cold.  Clear skies.  Saw geese nesting in the marsh.
Clear skies- very windy + choppy water.
Clear skies- no wind.  Scum on the water- lots of algae.
Clear + sunny.  Slight ripple in water.  Saw our first baby loon-also maybe 10-12 herons.
Clear- sunny- slight ripple- saw a pair of loons with 2 young.
Partly cloudy- windy- water a little rough.
Clear sky- water is calm- lots algae.
Slight ripples on the water- cloud cover moved in.
Mostly cloudy- wind is blowing- 4" waves.
Partly cloudy- water is very choppy.
Clear sky- light ripple on the water.
Ice off 4-18-95- water is calm- cloud cover is 85%.
Cloud cover 10%- water calm- saw a loon nest in the channel between McCann + Island Lake.
Calm + sunny- less than 5% cloud cover.
Slight ripple- 0% cloud cover- lots of boat traffic over the 4th weekend.
Hot- hazy- 40% cloud cover- light ripple- some algae.
Slight ripple- 5% cloud cover- some algae + floating weeds.  Heavy boat traffic over weekend.
Slight ripple- 75% cloud cover- weather changing fast- some algae + floating weeds.
6.38" rain since 8-4-95.  Slight ripple- 10% cloud cover- water murky- lot of floating junk.  The two baby loons are doing well.
Light ripple on the lake- 5% cloud cover- water is murky.  Lots of boat traffic this weekend.  We had 9.75 inches of rain in the month of August.
Light ripple- 20% cloud cover- green slime on lake.
Sunny- light ripple- 0% cloud cover- lots of algae.  Saw a young loon.
Slight breeze and no cloud cover.
Cloud cover- 2%- breezy.  Bottom sample- no depth reported- assumed 48'.
30 % cloud cover- sunny- slight ripple. Saw a baby loon. It is as large as an adult.
Cloud cover 35%- lake calm. ( ) all 4 lakes today- we saw 11 loons today- only 2 were young ones.
10% cloud cover- choppy water- lots of floating algae.
First reading of the year- disappointed in some of chemistry  - cloud cover 15%.
Light ripple- sunny- 0% cloud cover- loons are nesting in the channel again.
Sunny- windy- 3 inch waves.  5% cloud cover.
Slightly hazy light ripple 80% cloud cover.
Ice off 4-4-99.  Calm 40% cloud cover. Both eagles on nest.
Sunny- clear-  % cloud cover.  Two baby eagles on nest.
Sunny- light haze- windy with 3" waves.
Sunny- clear- light ripple 15 % cloud cover.
Ice off 3/25/2000.  Sunny- cold- windy- 75% cloud cover.  Saw one loon.
Sunny- breezy- light ripple- and 5 percent cloud cover.
Sunny- windy with 3" waves- 20 percent cloud cover.
Sunny- breezy- and 40 percent cloud cover.
Sunny- light ripple- 0 percent cloud cover.
Sunny- light ripple- 60 percent cloud cover.
90% cloud cover.  Weather changed fast.  Got reading with a break in the cloud cover.
Calm and sunny.  75% cloud cover.  Algae level very high.
70 percent cloud cover- windy- 4" waves.  Eagle sitting in tree by nest.
35 percent cloud cover- sunny- breezy and light ripple.  Eagle soaring overhead.
0% cloud cover.  Sunny- calm. Algae levels very high.
75% cloud cover- very windy.  Water very choppy.
Water very calm- 2% cloud cover.  A very light haze.
Sunny- 10% cloud cover- light breeze- saw two sand hill cranes- two loons- coats teal and mergansers in channel and the ice was off on 4/26/2001.
Sunny- no clouds. Light ripple. Saw a pair of geese with 7 little ones- first of the year.
45% cloud cover. Windy- 4" waves. 3" rain since 6/10/01.
No clouds- light haze- and calm.
Partly cloudy with a 50% cloud cover- sunny- and lots of boat traffic making 4" waves on the water.
Cloud cover 50%. Light haze. Very calm.
Sunny with a 75% cloud cover- and there is light ripples on the water.
Calm- sunny- no clouds- and lots of boat traffic.
Sunny- calm- clear with no clouds- and the algae levels are very high.
Sunny- calm and clear with a 5% cloud cover.
Sunny- calm and clear with no clouds.
Sunny- calm- and there is a 10% cloud cover.
Sunny- no clouds- and light breeze.
No clouds- sunny- and light ripple.
95% cloud cover- sunshine when we left home. Windy and wavy. Ice OFF 4-17-02
15% cloud cover. Light ripple. Boat traffic light for a holiday.
No clouds- light haze- water calm.
No clouds- sunny- breezy and light waves
20% cloud cover. Sunny. Wind has picked up since we started- lot of waves
20% cloud cover- sunny- clear- and calm
Sunny- light haze. 30% cloud cover. Wind picking up.
20% cloud cover- sunny- water a little rough.
Cloud cover 20%- sunny- windy.  Ice off 4/14/2003.
Clear- warm- slight breeze from North
Hazy sun- 0-2 mph breeze.  Some algae evident.
85 F- sunny- SW 10-15 mph.  Some suspended algae.

Very high algae content and lots of floating aquatic debris.
Beautiful fall day.  Light winds- clear sky.
Very Breezy-  Temps in the upper 80's.  A few clouds.  Saw Eagles and Sea Gulls.

Partly cloudy- Curly Leaf Pondweed plentiful.
